4:
Trick or treaaat! And trust us, you
DON'T want the trick! Heh.
6:
All right you rascals. Here's one for
you too, Corinna. Happy Halloween!
10:
F-for me? I appreciate it, but I'm just
chaperoning...
13:
I doubt anyone would mind if you
did some trick-or-treating yourself,
Corinna.
17:
I mind! As a cleric, I need to be a
good role model—and that means
no goofing around when I'm
supervising children.
20:
B-besides, it's not like I want to
trick-or-treat or anything, even if it
DOES look fun. F-for kids, of course!
24: Ow! I didn't mean to block the road...
32:
Yes, I was just caught me off guard,
is all.
38: Oh... Oh no, I think my wallet's gone!
41:
It must've fallen out of my basket!
Wh-what should I do?
45:
For starters, take a deeeep breath,
and then let's try retracing your
steps.
48:
I'm afraid I haven't seen it. I know it's
not much by way of consolation, but
here. I hope this helps cheer you up
a little.
51:
Flowers? Th-they're lovely, but these
are supposed to be for sale, right? I
couldn't possibly...
54:
Shhh, none of that now, dear. You're
always so sweet to us merchants.
56:
Yeah, even if luck's not on your side
today, we've always got your back.
Hope this helps!
59:
Ohhh, you're all too kind... Thank you
so much!
64:
Still no sign of it, and... 
*sigh* It's my own fault I lost it, but 
people keep trying to cheer me up 
with sweets and presents...
67:
Hmmm... I checked with the Guild,
but no one's brought it to the
lost-and-found. We'll just have to
keep asking around.
71:
Hi, sorry, do you have a moment?
We're looking for—
74:
N-nope! Haven't seen the angel girl's
wallet!
78:
...No one's said anything about a
wallet yet.
82:
I remember you. You're the one who
ran into Corinna earlier.
92:
H-HEEELP! Someone stop that man!
He stole my wallet!
98:
On the count of three.
One, two, three... BOO!
104:
F-found you!
Wait, what are you three doing here?
107:
We've got you cornered now! Hand
over the wallet!
114:
I've got a whooole arsenal of
Halloween tricks ready for
troublemakers like you!
120:
Whew, awesome work, gang! We've
been trying to catch that nasty old
purse-nabber for weeks.
123:
Which means—drumroll please—
a nice! Big! BOUNTYYY!
128:
Wait! The merchants at the street
fair are the ones who caught him.
We just helped a little.
131:
Well, I WAS gonna split the cash
between everyone, but they insisted
it all go to you.
134:
After all, we never woulda caught
him without help from the three
spoOoOokiest ghosties in town!
137:
Yaaay! Corinna, does this mean we
can get a pumpkin pie for the party?
139:
Wait, don't waste it on pie! I wanna
buy a sword! Pleeeease? I'll get
super strong and protect everyone!
142:
Wh-whoa! Let's not get TOO excited,
now.
146:
But I guess it won't hurt to splurge a
liiittle. We'll have the best Halloween
ever!
152:
Ahaha, right behind you! Trick or
treaaat!
